The paper discusses a method for transaction processing in databases, which is a core topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The approach is lock-free and scalable, which suggests that it may be relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of declarative languages and functional data structures, which are topics in programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper uses techniques from worst-case optimal algorithms and fixpoint equations, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
